# Mission plan

**Execution model:** Squad Leader collects a developer-confirmed quick-fix bullet list, spawns a **Quick Fix Plan agent** that scaffolds a minimal parent plan and runs **`new-plan`** + **`pr-plan`** inline. **`pr-plan`** spawns **`coding-session`** (§5d). Ship execution stays on the detached **`coding-session`** lane; the Squad Leader tracks planning closure and ship progress, then proposes dispatch resolution.

**Skill reuse:** [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/`](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/) — **`quick-fix-plan`** (§3 spawn), **`new-plan`**, **`pr-plan`**, **`coding-session`**. Spawn contracts: [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/README.md`](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/README.md).

## Mission constraints (binding)

| Constraint | Rule |
|------------|------|
| **Scope** | Small fixes — cosmetic UI/styling and **simple functional changes**; few lines per item |
| **Complexity** | **≤6** — developer **must** only task this dispatch with low-complexity work |
| **Developer responsibility** | Developer confirms each dispatch item is complexity **6 or under** before opening; agent validates at intake |
| **Intake** | Short bullet list **or** free-form fix description (prose path synthesizes bullets for confirmation); items may be unrelated but each must qualify under scope and complexity |
| **PR count** | **Exactly one** PR plan per dispatch (single indexed child) |
| **Skipped** | Full **`author-prd`**, **`master-planner`** Master Plan, **`pr-breakdown`**, **`delivery-phases`**, **`phase-planner`** |
| **Out of scope redirect** | Complexity **>6**, multi-PR decomposition, or work needing Master Plan → **`plan and deliver a single phase`** (**1–6** PRs, complexity **≤ 20**) or **`plan and deliver`** (detached dispatch) |
| **Ship chain** | Same detached **`coding-session`** order as plan-and-deliver §8 |

### Operations filesystem invariant (binding)

All **`.sedea/operations/`** writes from the **main hosting clone** only — see [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/0_hosting-repo.mdc`](.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/0_hosting-repo.mdc) § **Operations persistence (main hosting root only)**.

### Worktree removal ownership (binding)

Same as plan-and-deliver — [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/0_hosting-repo.mdc`](.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/0_hosting-repo.mdc) § *Worktree ownership*; rule **20** § *Worktree removal ownership* in [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/rules/20_efficient-pr-shipping.mdc`](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/rules/20_efficient-pr-shipping.mdc).

### Post-PR review inheritance (binding)

Detached **`coding-session`** ship chains reuse plan-and-deliver mechanics — this wrapper does **not** own PR review-cycle steps. After **`create-pr`**, the inline **`pr-review`** / **`pr-review.mjs`** boundary from [plan-and-deliver/plan.mdc § Post-PR handoff](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/plan.mdc) applies unchanged. Do **not** restate the review procedure here; when the developer picks **`start-pr-review`**, load [plan-and-deliver `pr-review/SKILL.md`](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/pr-review/SKILL.md) via [Post-create-pr handoff gate](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md#post-create-pr-handoff-gate).

### Repo rules ship inheritance (binding)

Detached **`coding-session`** lanes execute canonical plan-and-deliver repo-rules behavior — this wrapper does **not** duplicate reconcile or post-review rule-update steps. **Pre-PR:** [plan-and-deliver `coding-session/SKILL.md` § *Repo rules reconciliation (binding)*](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md#repo-rules-reconciliation-binding) and [Repo rules reconciliation gate](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md#repo-rules-reconciliation-gate) — plan §5 → **`.cursor/rules/*.mdc`** before ship cut-point. **Post-review:** when inline **`pr-review`** classifies **Rule-update required**, follow [Post-review repo rules handoff](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md#post-review-repo-rules-handoff) after the disposition gate — see [plan-and-deliver `pr-review/SKILL.md`](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/pr-review/SKILL.md).

**Parallel `hosting-repo-rules` fork (cross-ref only):** When product **`coding-session`** terminals carry **`repoRulesReconciliationStatus: pending`**, parent **`master-planner`** / **`phase-planner`** may fire-and-forget spawn **`hosting-repo-rules`** per canonical [plan-and-deliver `coding-session/SKILL.md` § *Spawner spawn-detection outputs*](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md#spawner-spawn-detection-outputs) and [plan-and-deliver/plan.mdc §8 detached branches](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/plan.mdc). This wrapper inherits that contract — **no duplicate spawn prose here**.

## Objectives

1. **Quick-fix intake** — Collect developer-confirmed scope via **`provide-list`** (bullet list) or **`description-of-fix`** (free-form prose synthesized into bullets for confirmation); each item is a small fix with complexity **≤6**.

2. **Single PR plan** — Produce one PR plan under `.sedea/operations/` via minimal parent scaffold, **`new-plan`** (indexed child), and **`pr-plan`** inline (§§1–4 populated).

3. **Standard ship** — Hand off to **`coding-session`** for implementation and the full plan-and-deliver ship chain (worktree, cut-point, deploy-walk, pre-pr-review, create-pr, pr-review, post-merge cleanup, optional plan-reconcile).

4. **Squad Leader oversight** — Track planning completion and detached ship progress; gate **`mission_control_propose_dispatch_resolution`**.

