## Checkpoint turn UX (mission protocol)

Under Checkpoint trust (`trustLevel: checkpoint`), auto-advance scripted happy-path steps on the **Squad Leader** lane; emit structured choice only at **USER_CHECKPOINT** markers in protocol steps below, **#external-wait** spawn-and-wait surfaces, or exception paths. **No cross-skill inheritance** — gate defaults here apply only to this mission **`plan.mdc`**; child skills document their own markers.

Marker syntax: [`.sedea/centers/sedea/docs/user-checkpoint-marker-syntax.md`](.sedea/centers/sedea/docs/user-checkpoint-marker-syntax.md).

| Protocol § | Checkpoint behavior | Gate |
|------------|---------------------|------|
| **§1** Open dispatch | Auto-advance when phrase matches | USER_CHECKPOINT on phrase mismatch |
| **§2** Collect quick fix intake | **Gate** — first developer-pick on leader | USER_CHECKPOINT — pick intake mode and confirm scope |
| **§2.5** Brainstorm (optional) | **Waiting** after spawn; auto-chain §3 on approved report | **#external-wait** before turn end; USER_CHECKPOINT on failure/partial |
| **§3** Quick Fix Plan spawn | **Waiting** — child owns planning lane | **#external-wait** after spawn; USER_CHECKPOINT on failure/partial |
| **§4** Minimal parent and PR plan | Inline on child — not Squad Leader | Blocked → terminal partial/failure to leader |
| **§5** Coding session (detached) | Off leader lane — **`pr-plan`** §5d spawn | — |
| **§6** Planning closure ack | Auto-advance status ack only | — |
| **§7** Ship cadence ledger | Auto-advance ack while ship rows stay open | USER_CHECKPOINT — pre-resolution checklist; planning-only close |
| **§8** Dispatch resolution | **Gate** when planning and ship allow | USER_CHECKPOINT — approve dispatch resolution |

## Protocol

### 1. Infer intent from the opening command phrase

- **Type:** Branching logic
- **Intent:** Match **`quick fix`** and prepare intake.
- **Inputs:** Opening message; **`mission.yaml`** command inventory.
- **Expected output:** Intent **`quick-fix`**; optional scope remainder for §2.
- **Next-step resolution:** Phrase matches → §2 (auto-advance). No match → USER_CHECKPOINT gate below.

USER_CHECKPOINT — confirm mission intent when the opening command phrase does not match.

**Procedure**

1. Match **`quick fix`** case-insensitively (longest phrase first per [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/4_mission.mdc`](.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/4_mission.mdc) § **Mission command phrases**).
2. When dispatch scope is readable from the opening message (command remainder), run **Dispatch display refresh** (above) — **skip** when current dispatch chrome already matches.
3. Strip the phrase; pass remainder as optional scope hint to §2.
4. Continue to §2.

### 2. Collect quick fix intake

- **Type:** Branching logic
- **Intent:** Gather confirmed quick-fix scope on the Squad Leader lane before §3 spawn — via bullet list or free-form fix description.
- **Inputs:** Opening remainder; Mission Control dispatch binding; `intakeMode` (`provide-list` | `description-of-fix`).
- **Expected output:** `intakeMode`, `changeList` (non-empty confirmed bullet list), optional `changeDescription` (when prose path used), `complexityConfirmed: true` (each item ≤6), `scopeConfirmed: true`, optional `title`.
- **Next-step resolution:** List confirmed in scope and complexity → §3 (auto-advance). Out-of-scope or complexity **>6** → USER_CHECKPOINT gate below.

USER_CHECKPOINT — pick quick-fix intake mode and confirm scope before spawn.

**Procedure**

1. **Intake mode (required first):** Open structured choice on the Squad Leader lane:
   - **`provide-list`** — I'll paste my bullet list next — proceed to collect it
   - **`description-of-fix`** — free-form prose with all details of what to change and do (collect on follow-up turn, or same turn when opening remainder already contains the description)
   - **`brainstorm-first`** — optional research session → report → auto-chain §3 **`quick-fix-plan`** (§2.5)
   - **`redirect-scope`** — out of scope or complexity **>6** → **`plan and deliver a single phase`** or **`plan and deliver`** (detached)
   - **`pause`**
   - **More details for option _**
   When the developer selects **`brainstorm-first`**, run §2.5 and **skip** steps 2–9 until brainstorm completes or abandons.
2. **`provide-list` path:** Collect **bullet list** of changes — required; may pre-fill from opening remainder when bullets are already present.
3. **`description-of-fix` path:** Collect **free-form prose** (`changeDescription`) — required; do not infer missing details from title alone. Propose a **synthesized bullet list** derived from the prose; present for developer review with structured choice before scope/complexity gates. When the developer chooses **revise intake** at that confirmation, return to step 1 — they may re-enter prose for re-synthesis, switch to **`provide-list`**, or edit the synthesized bullets inline before re-running steps 4–9.
4. **Scope gate:** Confirm each item is a small fix — cosmetic UI/styling/copy **or** a **simple functional change** within this mission's line-count expectations. Reject items that need Master Plan decomposition, multiple PRs, or broad refactors.
5. **Complexity gate:** Confirm developer attests each item is complexity **6 or under**. When any item likely exceeds **6**, stop and offer redirect (see **Mission constraints**).
6. Collect optional **title** for the plan tree (default from first bullet, prose summary, or user phrase).
7. Present summary (title, final bullet list, complexity attestation, intake mode used); open structured choice to proceed to Quick Fix Plan agent, **revise intake** (return to step 1 per step 3), redirect scope, or pause.
8. When intake confirms a **title** that improves the dispatch title, re-run **Dispatch display refresh** (§ above) — **skip** when current dispatch chrome already matches.
9. **Forbidden:** spawn before list is confirmed in scope and complexity (both paths).

### 2.5 Brainstorm research (optional — `brainstorm-first`)

- **Type:** Agent engagement and handover
- **execution:** spawned
- **Intent:** Optional research before quick-fix intake; approved report synthesizes §3 **`quick-fix-plan`** bullets.
- **Trigger:** Developer selects **`brainstorm-first`** at §2 step 1.
- **Assigned skill:** [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/brainstorm-research/SKILL.md`](../plan-and-deliver/skills/brainstorm-research/SKILL.md)
- **Inputs:** `invokerMissionSlug: quick-fix`, `operationsDocsDirectory` from lane identity, optional seeds from §1.
- **Next-step resolution:**
  - Terminal **`developerApprovedReport: true`** → derive `changeList` bullets from report §5 Handoff summary, set `intakeMode: provide-list`, `complexityConfirmed` / `scopeConfirmed` after developer attestation in §3 spawn **`initiatingPrompt`** → **auto-chain §3** (no repeat §2 USER_CHECKPOINT).
  - **`abandonMission: true`** → call MCP **`mission_control_propose_dispatch_resolution`** with status **`abandoned`**.
  - Otherwise → USER_CHECKPOINT gate below.

USER_CHECKPOINT — pick next step when brainstorm child reports failure or partial.

**Procedure**

1. Emit **`mission_control_spawn_agent`** for **`brainstorm-research`** with **`warmUpRules`** including **`quick-fix/plan.mdc`** (§§1–2.5).
2. Open **next-step resume** structured choice (**#external-wait**) before ending the turn.
3. On terminal **`developerApprovedReport: true`**, compile §3 **`quick-fix-plan`** spawn **`inputs`** from report outputs and emit §3 spawn without re-collecting §2 fields on the leader lane.
4. On **`abandonMission: true`**, propose dispatch resolution — do not spawn §3.

### 3. Spawn Quick Fix Plan agent

- **Type:** Agent engagement and handover
- **execution:** spawned
- **Intent:** Delegate minimal parent scaffold and **`new-plan`** + **`pr-plan`** inline to a focused planning agent.
- **Target agent role:** Quick Fix Plan agent
- **skillPath (binding):** [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/quick-fix/skills/quick-fix-plan/SKILL.md`](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/quick-fix/skills/quick-fix-plan/SKILL.md) — host **`mission_control_spawn_agent`** uses this single path per [spawn contracts README](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/README.md) § *Universal spawn preflight*.
- **Inline on child lane (not separate spawns):** [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/new-plan/SKILL.md`](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/new-plan/SKILL.md), [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/pr-plan/SKILL.md`](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/pr-plan/SKILL.md) — executed per §4 inside the **`quick-fix-plan`** child lane.
- **Required rule context:** Sedea baseline, **this `plan.mdc`**, **`development-process.md`**, [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/rules/30_planning-target-resolution.mdc`](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/rules/30_planning-target-resolution.mdc), plan-and-deliver **`skills/README.md`**.
- **Inputs:** `intakeMode` (`provide-list` | `description-of-fix`), `changeList`, optional `changeDescription` (required when `intakeMode` is `description-of-fix`), `title` from Mission Control, `centerSlug: research-and-development`, `complexityConfirmed: true`.
- **Expected output:** Child terminal with `outputs.parentPlanPath`, `outputs.parentPlanSlug`, `outputs.targetPlanPath`, `outputs.targetPlanSlug`, `outputs.readyForImplementation`, `outputs.implementationHandoffStatus`, `outputs.prPlanHandoffReady`, optional `outputs.spawnCorrelationId` / `outputs.codingSessionStatus` after inline **`pr-plan`** §5d — per **`quick-fix-plan/SKILL.md`** **`## Completion (spawned)`** and **`## Checkpoint turn UX (skill-local)`**.
- **Next-step resolution:** Emit spawn → **#external-wait** before turn end; on child terminal success with PR plan path → §6 ack on leader (auto-advance). Failure/partial → USER_CHECKPOINT gate below.

USER_CHECKPOINT — pick next step when Quick Fix Plan child reports failure or partial.

**Spawn preflight**

- **`skillPath`:** `.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/quick-fix/skills/quick-fix-plan/SKILL.md` (workspace-relative on emit).
- **`name`** / **`description`** from intake **title** or first bullet — not generic placeholders.
- **`initiatingPrompt`:** one narrative prompt string weaving the confirmed bullet list, scope/complexity confirmation, and full `changeDescription` when the prose intake path was used — not separate structured sub-fields.
- **`warmUpRules`:** include **`quick-fix/plan.mdc`** instead of **`plan-and-deliver/plan.mdc`**.

**Procedure**

1. Compile child **`inputs`** from §2: `intakeMode`, `changeList`, optional `changeDescription`, `title`, `centerSlug`, `complexityConfirmed`.
2. Set **`initiatingPrompt`** with the confirmed bullet list, scope/complexity attestation, and full prose when the **`description-of-fix`** path was used.
3. Run [spawn contracts README](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/README.md) § *Universal spawn preflight*; set **`name`** from intake **title** or first bullet — not generic placeholders.
4. Emit exactly one **`mission_control_spawn_agent`** for **`quick-fix-plan`** with dispatch-unique `slug` and preflight **`inputs`**.
5. Open **next-step resume** structured choice (**#external-wait**) before ending the turn.
6. Stop until Mission Control delivers **`mission_control_send_agent_result`** for the spawn.
7. On terminal success with PR plan path, continue §6 ack on the leader lane (auto-advance). On failure/partial, apply USER_CHECKPOINT gate above.

### 4. Minimal parent and PR plan (Quick Fix Plan agent lane)

- **Type:** Simple skill execution (Quick Fix Plan agent — not Squad Leader)
- **execution:** inline on child lane
- **Intent:** Create one PR plan without full Master Plan / **`master-planner`** / **`pr-breakdown`**.
- **Inputs:** §3 spawn `inputs` and `initiatingPrompt`.
- **Expected output:** One parent plan with single **`### PR list`** row; one PR plan stub populated through **`pr-plan`** §§1–4; handoff ready for **`coding-session`**.
- **Next-step resolution:** Success → inline **`pr-plan`** §5c gate then §5d spawn **`coding-session`** on §5 (**#external-wait** on detached child). Blocked → terminal partial/failure to leader per **`quick-fix-plan/SKILL.md`** **`## Checkpoint turn UX (skill-local)`**.

**Procedure (Quick Fix Plan agent)**

1. **Resolve `HOSTING_ROOT`**; operations writes on main hosting clone only.
2. **Minimal parent plan** — scaffold under `.sedea/operations/.../plans/` with:
   - Title from intake **`title`**
   - **`### PR list`** with **exactly one** row summarizing the bullet list as a single quick-fix concern
   - Sidecar **`parent: null`**, **`status: started`** per [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/8_plan-board-contract.mdc`](.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/8_plan-board-contract.mdc)
3. **`new-plan`** inline — `mode: indexed-child`, `childKind: pr-plan`, `index: 1`, parent paths from step 2.
4. **`pr-plan`** inline — populate §§1–4 from bullet list; §§5–8 remain **`_TBD_`** for **`coding-session`** (normative).
5. At **`pr-plan`** §5c/§5d — spawn **`coding-session`** with planning handoff `inputs` (`readyForImplementation`, `targetPlanPath`, `upstreamSkill: pr-plan`, etc.) per **`pr-plan/SKILL.md`**.
6. Emit child terminal **`mission_control_send_agent_result`** with plan paths and handoff status.

**Forbidden on this lane:** **`master-planner`**, **`pr-breakdown`**, **`delivery-phases`**, **`phase-planner`**, second PR row, Squad Leader **`mission_control_propose_dispatch_resolution`**.

### 5. Coding session (detached)

- **Type:** Mission dispatch (detached) from Squad Leader perspective
- **Intent:** Implementation and ship chain on **`coding-session`** lane spawned by **`pr-plan`** §5d.
- **Inputs:** Spawn `inputs` from **`pr-plan`**; bullet list in `initiatingPrompt`.
- **Expected output:** Ship milestones via **`coding-session`** terminal re-emits per plan-and-deliver §8.
- **Next-step resolution:** Leader §7 tracks host-sync ship rows; §8 when gates allow.

**Detached branches** — identical order to [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/plan.mdc`](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/plan.mdc) §8 detached table: **`coding-session`** → before deploy **`deploy-walk`** → **`pre-pr-review`** spawn → **`create-pr`** → **`pr-review`** → post-merge cleanup → after deploy **`deploy-walk`** → explicit **`plan-reconcile`**. **`pre-pr-review`** reviewer lane auto-advances Steps **1–8** under Checkpoint trust — parent **`coding-session`** owns post-review developer gates per **`pre-pr-review/SKILL.md`** § *Checkpoint turn UX*.

The Squad Leader **does not** spawn **`coding-session`** from §§1–3. The **Quick Fix Plan agent** child lane spawns **`coding-session`** via inline **`pr-plan`** §5d — same ownership contract as **`master-planner`** on plan-and-deliver (see **`../plan-and-deliver/skills/README.md`** § *Common mistake — Squad Leader redirect*).

### 6. Planning closure acknowledgement

- **Type:** Finish/stop logic
- **Intent:** Acknowledge Quick Fix Plan agent terminal; register PR plan path on planning ledger.
- **Inputs:** §3 child **`mission_control_send_agent_result`**.
- **Expected output:** One-line status ack; open ship row when `readyForImplementation` reported.
- **Next-step resolution:** Continue §7; do not re-run planning on leader lane.

### 7. Ship cadence ledger

- **Type:** Finish/stop logic
- **Intent:** Track detached **`coding-session`** ship progress; gate dispatch resolution.
- **Inputs:** Host-sync **`Mission Control: ship-ledger sync (section 8).`** messages; **`ship-ledger.v1.json`** when present.

Same automation contract as plan-and-deliver §8 (*Mission Control host sync*) when the host registers mission slug **`quick-fix`**. **Forbidden:** manual Ship recap paste on the leader lane.

- **Next-step resolution:**
  - Open ship rows with host-sync updates → auto-advance ack; gate §8 when rows close.
  - Open/blocked rows without host-sync this session → USER_CHECKPOINT gate below before §8 resolution.
  - Planning complete with no ship row yet → USER_CHECKPOINT — planning-only vs active ship.

USER_CHECKPOINT — pick planning-only close vs keep ship active when pre-resolution checklist fails.

**Pre-resolution checklist:** Before **`mission_control_propose_dispatch_resolution`**, re-scan ship rows — do not propose **`resolved`** while `open`/`blocked` rows lack host-sync this session unless developer chose planning-only close via USER_CHECKPOINT gate above.

### 8. Dispatch resolution (Squad Leader)

- **Type:** Finish/stop logic
- **Intent:** Close dispatch when objectives met or user signals wrap-up.
- **Expected output:** `mission_control_propose_dispatch_resolution` with `status` and `summary`.
- **Next-step resolution:** Planning and ship gates allow → USER_CHECKPOINT gate below; otherwise auto-advance ledger ack only.

USER_CHECKPOINT — approve dispatch resolution when planning and ship gates allow.

Per [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/4_mission.mdc`](.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/4_mission.mdc) § **Dispatch resolution**. Use **`resolved`** when planning and ship complete; **`partial`** when PR open or follow-up remains.

